Process Control System Simulation (PCSS) Group (9/10 - 6/11) Review and maintain the Sim Suite simulation code for the Pine Bluff Chemical Demilitarization Facility (PBCDF). Update and test the simulator code to ensure that the behavior matches that of the actual control system at the site. This requires that the observation be verified and the behavior corrected, as needed. Ensure that new or modified designs are properly documented and meet all applicable electrical codes and safety regulations. Serve as technical lead on all projects involving electrical controls, PLCs and/or HMIs, ensuring continuous progress and quality results to meet customer requirements. Consult with customers regarding current technical issues. Then investigate, analyze, troubleshoot, and finally recommend solutions to correct these technical issues. Actively share knowledge and skills with T&E team members, as well as other support personnel. Conduct and participate in formal and informal training with teams and individuals in areas of expertise.
